COMMON SYNTAX MODIFICATIONS FOR ALL PROGRAMS
================================================================================

1) if block
Why: Used when one condition must be checked.

Syntax:
if condition:
    statement


2) if-else block
Why: Used when there are two possibilities.

Syntax:
if condition:
    statement
else:
    statement


3) if-elif-else block
Why: Used when there are multiple conditions.

Syntax:
if condition1:
    statement
elif condition2:
    statement
else:
    statement


4) for loop
Why: Used when number of repetitions is known.

Syntax:
for i in range(start, end):
    statement


5) while loop
Why: Used when program should continue until condition becomes false.

Syntax:
while condition:
    statement


6) function
Why: Reuses code and avoids repetition.

Syntax:
def function_name(parameters):
    statements
    return value


7) class
Why: Groups data and functions together.

Syntax:
class ClassName:
    def __init__(self):
        statements

    def method_name(self):
        statements


8) try-except
Why: Handles runtime errors safely.

Syntax:
try:
    risky_code
except ExceptionName:
    error_message


9) list
Why: Stores multiple values in order.

Syntax:
my_list = [10, 20, 30]


10) dictionary
Why: Stores key-value pairs.

Syntax:
my_dict = {"name": "Rahul", "marks": 90}


11) input
Why: Takes value from user.

Syntax:
name = input("Enter name: ")
num = int(input("Enter number: "))


12) import library/module
Why: Uses extra functionality from Python libraries.

Syntax:
import module_name
from module_name import function_name


