IMPORTANT EXAM/VIVA LOGIC TO REMEMBER
================================================================================

1) Sort graph/data safely:
Use zip() when two lists are connected.

Example:
data = list(zip(names, marks))
data.sort(key=lambda x: x[1])
names, marks = zip(*data)

Why:
Because marks and names must move together.

2) Sort dictionary by values:
sorted_data = sorted(my_dict.items(), key=lambda x: x[1])

Why:
Dictionary stores data as key-value pairs. x[1] means value.

3) Find max value key in dictionary:
topper = max(students, key=students.get)

Why:
students.get gives marks for each name.

4) Read and write file:
with open("data.txt", "w") as f:
    f.write("Hello")

Why:
with automatically closes the file.

5) Regular expression:
re.findall(pattern, text)

Why:
Finds all matching patterns from text.

6) DataFrame filtering:
df[df["Salary"] > 75000]

Why:
Returns only rows where condition is true.

7) NumPy sorting:
np.sort(arr)

Why:
Sorts array elements in ascending order.

8) Matplotlib show graph:
plt.show()

Why:
Displays the plotted graph window.
